   @{"  Known Bugs       " link "bugs"} - What should I lookout for?

@Endnode
@Node "Intro" "Introduction"

@{b}Introduction@{ub}
~~~~~~~~~~~~

@{b}@{i}Why another "text to guide" utility ?@{ub}@{ui}

Well I searched for a utility where you were able to make amigaguidefiles
easily. I found a couple of programs but however they either didn't work
or they were hard to use.

So I decided to program a utility where you just converts the textfile into
an amigaguidefile by following some easy rules.

@Endnode
@Node "Requirements"

@{b}Requirements@{ub}
~~~~~~~~~~~~

Saint Guide may be started from workbench or cli and requires KS 2.04 (V37)
or higher.  If you start from WB it requires @{"reqtools.library" link "credits"} V38
or higher

@Endnode
@Node "howtoedit" "How to edit"

@{b}How to edit@{ub}
~~~~~~~~~~~

Saint Guide simply "converts" special-edited textfiles into amigaguide
format. The rules are quite simple to understand.

  @{" . " link "Nodes"}  - Node-character.
  @{" ` " link "Links"}  - Link-character.
  @{" ; " link "Remarks"}  - Remark-character.

  @{" ¹ " link "Other"}  - Bold-character.
  @{" ² " link "Other"}  - Italic-character.
  @{" ³ " link "Other"}  - Underline-character.

@Endnode
@Node Nodes

@{b}Nodes@{ub}
~~~~~

To start a node you just have to have a "." in the beginning of a  line
and then a string follows wich is the node-name.

i.e.
."Main-Index"        will be converted to:  "@Node "Main-Index".
."Bun" "Main-Index"         ==>             "@Node "Bun" "Main-Index".

Note that the second string will just be a titlestring and the first string
is the nodename. The titlestring is optional.

@{b}NOTE!@{ub} The "." @{b}must@{ub} be in the beginning of the line.

You don't have to think of where to end a node. Whenever a new node is
started the previous node is ended.

@Endnode
@Node Links

@{b}Links@{ub}
~~~~~

To make a link you just have to like this:

 Index... index
this will be the same as: {" Index... " link "index"} (With a "@" first).

This will make a linkbutton named " Index... " that leads to the node
"index"

If SGuide just finds two "`" on one line it will ignore them and go on
converting.

                     -=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-

@{b}REMEMBER!@{ub}

- You may not use tab's in linknames.
- You may not @{b}bold@{ub}/@{i}italic@{ui}/@{u}underline@{uu} a link.

@Endnode
@Node Remarks

@{b}Remarks@{ub}
~~~~~~~

To put in your own little remarks you just have to put a ";" in the
beginning of a line and the whole line is yours. It will @{b}not@{ub} be shown
when reading the guidefile.
@Endnode
@Node Other "Other features"

@{b}Other features@{ub}
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

"¹" turns on/off @{b}bold@{ub} typeface.
"²" turns on/off @{i}italic@{ui}.
"³" turns on/off @{u}underline@{uu}.

@Endnode
@Node "Usage" "How to use Saint Guide"

@{b}Usage@{ub}
~~~~~

If you start Saint Guide from workbench it will try to open @{"reqtools.library" link "credits"}
and let you select files to convert.  @{b}IF@{ub} there were errors it will tell
you about them all.  @{b}=)@{ub}  After converting one file it prints some
information about the file and then puts up a requester for saving the
guidefile.

If you start it from cli without any arguments it will do the same as
starting from workbench. But you may use arguments.

i.e.
@{" SGuide dh0:List.txt dh0:List.guide        " link "Ex1"}
@{" SGuide dh0:List.txt dh0:List.guide QUIET  " link "Ex2"}
@{" SGuide dh0:List.txt NOSAVE                " link "Ex3"}
@{" SGuide dh0:List.txt dh0:List.guide NOSAVE " link "Ex4"}
@{" SGuide REQ                                " link "Ex5"}

@Endnode
@Node Ex1 "Simple Convert"

@{b}SGuide dh0:List.txt dh0:List.guide@{ub}

This will convert "dh0:List.txt" and save it as "dh0:List.guide".

@Endnode
@Node Ex2 "Quiet Convert"

@{b}SGuide dh0:List.txt dh0:List.guide QUIET@{ub}

This will convert "dh0:List.txt" and save it as "dh0:List.guide". @{b}But@{ub} it
doesn't print any information about the saved object.

If REQ argument was selected, SGuide will just ask for file to load and
file to save.

@Endnode
@Node Ex3 "NoSave"

@{b}SGuide dh0:List.txt NOSAVE@{ub}

This will just and print some information about "dh0:List.txt". Without
saving anything.

@Endnode
@Node Ex4 "NoSave"

@{b}SGuide dh0:List.txt dh0:List.guide NOSAVE@{ub}

This will just and print some information about "dh0:List.txt" @{b}if@{ub} the
file was named "dh0:List.guide". Without saving anything.

@Endnode
@Node Ex5 "Reqtools"

@{b}SGuide REQ@{ub}

This will open reqtools and use it for filerequesting instead of using
arguments. If you use the NOSAVE or QUIET argument it will be used
using reqtools.

@Endnode
