@Node "History"

@{b}History@{ub}
~~~~~~~

 v1.05  - First release. Yes!

 v1.08  - Wrote a routine that prints out the original size, the new size,
          how many nodes that was included and how many nodes in the file.
        - Improved some main routines.

 v1.09b - Fixed a bug that occurs when allocating extra memory.

 v1.1b  - Fixed a little bug that occurs when converting hex numbers to
          decimalnumbers.
        - Improved the main Converting-routine.
        - Improved the routine that prints out the results about the
          converted files.
        - Wrote a routine that if the file that should have been converted
          were incorrect edited it prints all errors that occured in the
          file. This helps the user to discover his/hers faults easier.
        - Included the argument-options: -Q (QUIET) and -N (NOSAVE)
        - You may now put some remarks in your guidefile by using ";" in
          the beginning of a line.
        - It now prints out how many remarks it was in the converted file.

 v1.12  - Improved the routine that converts hex numbers to decimal
          numbers.
        - Fixed a "real" argumentroutine with a template, using ReadArgs().
        - Fixed so the program prints with RawDoFmt() in CLI.
        - You may now load reqtools.library from CLI with the argument REQ.
        - Improved the routine that checks if the file allready has a
          "guide" extend.
        - Fixed some minor bugs.

 v1.13  - Find out that I opened libraries with OldOpenLibrary(). Changed
          it to OpenLibrary().
        - I puted the code in chipmem only. Now either in chip or fast.
        - Optimized the routine that converts hex numbers into decimal
          numbers.

@Endnode
